			<div class="content" id="post-content-573637">
									

<p>It's an old joke.</p>
<p>"I want to name my [whatever] "they're on our side, sir!" and put it in big letters on [something visible]. the confusion should buy me time for a few extra shots."</p>
<p>The idea being that just as the battle commences, the commanding enemy officer will turn to someone and ask "what's that say?". cue confusion.</p>
<p>A fitting reference for a misinformation group, I think.</p>
<p>I'd always imagined G5 as the team whose job would be to sabotauge news crews/reports in cases of highly visible SCP activity in public areas. for example, if godzilla stormed central park, they'd be the small group of guys sedating cameramen and reporters, then administering amnesiacs and cover stories before they went on the air. You'd <em>need</em> a task force in that scenario. Undercover in various media sources probably means monitoring them for preparedness sake.</p>

							</div>

								
